## 4. Spatially Enabled DataFrame (SeDF)

### Concepto:
Extensión de Pandas DataFrame para trabajar con datos espaciales directamente.

### Operaciones:

```python
import pandas as pd
from arcgis.features import GeoAccessor, GeoSeriesAccessor

# Crear SeDF desde feature layer
sdf = pd.DataFrame.spatial.from_featureclass(r"C:\data\cities.shp")
# Desde feature layer URL
sdf = pd.DataFrame.spatial.from_layer(feature_layer)
# Desde CSV con coordenadas
df = pd.read_csv("data.csv")
sdf = pd.DataFrame.spatial.from_xy(df, "LONGITUDE", "LATITUDE")
# Desde GeoJSON
sdf = pd.DataFrame.spatial.from_featureclass("data.geojson")

# Propiedades espaciales
sdf.spatial.sr           # Sistema de referencia
sdf.spatial.bbox         # Bounding box
sdf.spatial.geometry_type # Tipo de geometría
sdf.spatial.area         # Áreas
sdf.spatial.length       # Longitudes
sdf.spatial.centroid     # Centroides
sdf.spatial.true_centroid # Centroide real

# Operaciones espaciales
sdf.spatial.buffer(distance=500)
sdf.spatial.clip(envelope)
sdf.spatial.dissolve(by="REGION")
sdf.spatial.erase(erase_sdf)
sdf.spatial.overlay(other_sdf, how="intersection")
sdf.spatial.project(spatial_reference)
sdf.spatial.relationship(other_sdf, relation="intersects")
sdf.spatial.select(other_sdf)

# Exportar
sdf.spatial.to_featureclass(r"C:\output\result.shp")
sdf.spatial.to_featurelayer("My Layer", gis=gis)
sdf.spatial.to_table(r"C:\output\table.csv")

# Visualización
sdf.spatial.plot(map_widget=m, renderer_type='c',  # classificación
                 method='esriClassifyNaturalBreaks',
                 class_count=5, col='POPULATION')
```

