## 5. Machine Learning y Deep Learning Geoespacial

### arcgis.learn Module

#### Detección de Objetos:
```python
from arcgis.learn import prepare_data, SingleShotDetector, RetinaNet, FasterRCNN, YOLOv3

# Preparar datos de entrenamiento
data = prepare_data(training_data, chip_size=448, batch_size=16)

# Entrenar modelo
model = SingleShotDetector(data, backbone="resnet50")
model.lr_find()  # Encontrar learning rate óptimo
model.fit(epochs=50, lr=0.001)

# Evaluar
model.average_precision_score()
model.show_results()

# Predecir
predictions = model.predict(test_raster)
```

#### Clasificación de Píxeles:
```python
from arcgis.learn import prepare_data, UnetClassifier, PSPNet, DeepLab

data = prepare_data(training_data, chip_size=256, class_mapping={1: "Water", 2: "Urban", 3: "Forest"})
model = UnetClassifier(data)
model.fit(epochs=25)
classified = model.predict(imagery_layer)
```

#### Detección de Cambios:
```python
from arcgis.learn import ChangeDetector
model = ChangeDetector(data)
model.fit(epochs=30)
changes = model.predict(before_image, after_image)
```

#### Clustering Espacial:
```python
from arcgis.features.analysis import find_point_clusters
# DBSCAN, HDBSCAN, Self-Adjusting
clusters = find_point_clusters(input_layer,
                                method="DBSCAN",
                                minimum_points=10,
                                search_distance="500 Meters")
```

#### Hot Spot Analysis:
```python
from arcgis.features.analysis import find_hot_spots
# Gi* de Getis-Ord
hot_spots = find_hot_spots(input_layer,
                           analysis_field="CRIME_COUNT",
                           bounding_polygon=study_area)
```

