## 6. GeoAnalytics (Big Data)

### Herramientas de GeoAnalytics Server:

| Herramienta | Descripción |
|-------------|-------------|
| Aggregate Points | Agregar puntos en bins/áreas |
| Join Features | Join espacial/temporal distribuido |
| Create Buffers | Buffers distribuidos |
| Reconstruct Tracks | Reconstruir tracks de GPS |
| Find Dwell Locations | Encontrar ubicaciones de permanencia |
| Detect Incidents | Detectar incidentes en datos temporales |
| Calculate Motion Statistics | Estadísticas de movimiento |
| Find Similar Locations | Ubicaciones similares (big data) |
| Forest-based Classification | Random Forest distribuido |
| GWR (Geographically Weighted Regression) | Regresión ponderada geográficamente |
| Snap Tracks | Alinear tracks a redes de carreteras |
| Describe Dataset | Estadísticas descriptivas del dataset |
| Clip Layer | Recortar por área |
| Dissolve Boundaries | Disolver límites |
| Overlay Layers | Superposición distribuida |

### Uso desde Python:
```python
from arcgis.geoanalytics import summarize_data, find_locations, analyze_patterns

# Aggregate Points a hexágonos
result = summarize_data.aggregate_points(
    point_layer=tracking_data,
    bin_type="HEXAGON",
    bin_size=1,
    bin_size_unit="Kilometers"
)

# Reconstruct Tracks
tracks = find_locations.reconstruct_tracks(
    input_layer=gps_points,
    track_fields=["VEHICLE_ID"],
    method="GEODESIC",
    time_split=15,
    time_split_unit="Minutes"
)
```

